  <description><![CDATA[<h2>Visit two contrasting parts of Switzerland on a multi-centre holiday to Lake Lucerne and Zermatt</h2>
<p>A multi-centre holiday to <a data-udi="umb://document/2e09d5bd5fae466db4b3c37d49150722" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2e09d5bd5fae466db4b3c37d49150722}" title="Zermatt">Zermatt</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/70b1a325037e4112bc5e6feeb41d725f" href="/{localLink:umb://document/70b1a325037e4112bc5e6feeb41d725f}" title="Lake Lucerne">Lake Lucerne</a> means you get to experience two contrasting regions of Switzerland on a holiday packed with spectacular views, culture and activity. Spend a couple of days exploring the chocolate-box town of Zermatt, famous as the home of the Matterhorn and enjoy a few days soaking up the sights of Lake Lucerne - explore the lake by paddle-steamer, take panoramic gondolas to the top of Mount Pilatus, and immerse yourself in the culture of the city.</p>
<h3>Guide price from: £1,795pp*</h3>
<h3>Your multi-centre holiday options: </h3>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Flexible durations in each destination</li>
<li>Travel and change destination on a Wednesday, Friday or Saturday</li>
<li>Option to spend the Lake Lucerne part of your holiday staying in either <a data-udi="umb://document/56819e7662924ccf91baa56999b5cbef" href="/{localLink:umb://document/56819e7662924ccf91baa56999b5cbef}" title="Lucerne">Lucerne</a> or <a data-udi="umb://document/e67e0510aeab481fa844cb74e63612a6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e67e0510aeab481fa844cb74e63612a6}" title="Weggis">Weggis</a></li>
</ul>
</ul>
<h3>Your holiday includes:</h3>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Return flights or trains from the UK</li>
<li>2nd class train transfers from the airport to your hotel in Lucerne/Weggis, between destinations and from your hotel in Zermatt to the airport (some changes of trains required, 1st class upgrade possible at extra cost. If you stay in Weggis part of your transfer will be by boat/bus)</li>
<li>Swiss Half Fare Card - worth over £100 – included as part of your rail tickets</li>
<li>Accommodation in your chosen hotel in each destination</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-12">
<div class="c-card c-card--generic c-card--generic-grey c-card--generic-shadow ">
