  <locationDescription><![CDATA[<p>A multi-centre holiday lets you mix and match hotels, lengths of stay, and exciting activities to create your ideal trip. Enjoy everything from panoramic walks, cultural tours and outdoor adventures to relaxing days and tasty local cuisine.</p>
<h3>Discover the beautiful city, lake and mountains of Lake Lucerne</h3>
<p>Lake Lucerne offers a little bit of everything Swiss, from the cultural city centre of Lucerne with its frescoed buildings and famous Chapel Bridge, to the picturesque waters of Lake Lucerne and the mountains and villages that surround it. Ride panoramic gondolas to the top of Mount Pilatus, or historic cog-wheel railway up Mount Rigi. The unique shape of Lake Lucerne spreads into four different cantons of Switzerland and the fleet of boats make easy work of exploring the huge variety of culture, scenery and activities this region has to offer. Choose to stay in the bustling city of <a data-udi="umb://document/56819e7662924ccf91baa56999b5cbef" href="/{localLink:umb://document/56819e7662924ccf91baa56999b5cbef}" title="Lucerne">Lucerne</a> or opt for a quieter stay in the scenic village of <a data-udi="umb://document/e67e0510aeab481fa844cb74e63612a6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e67e0510aeab481fa844cb74e63612a6}" title="Weggis">Weggis</a> a short boat ride from Lucerne. </p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/70b1a325037e4112bc5e6feeb41d725f" href="/{localLink:umb://document/70b1a325037e4112bc5e6feeb41d725f}" title="Lake Lucerne" class="c-btn c-btn--secondary c-btn c-btn--mid c-btn--secondary-hollow c-btn--wide u-text-center">Find Out More About Lake Lucerne</a></p>
<h3>Visit the Matterhorn village of Zermatt</h3>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/2e09d5bd5fae466db4b3c37d49150722" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2e09d5bd5fae466db4b3c37d49150722}" title="Zermatt">Zermatt</a> is a charming town full of rustic chalets and old farm buildings. It's famous for the Matterhorn mountain which first brought adventurous mountaineers to the region, as they attempted to climb it. Nowadays, holidays to Zermatt are still all about the mountains, but access is a lot easier thanks to the fantastic network of lifts and mountain trains. Ride the cog-wheel railway up to Gornergrat for the best view of the Matterhorn, or make the panoramic journey by cable-car over to Cervinia in Italy on the new Matterhorn Alpine Crossing. You can add up to two Inghams guided walks per week to your holiday in Zermatt too (subject to availability, terms and conditions apply).</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/2e09d5bd5fae466db4b3c37d49150722" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2e09d5bd5fae466db4b3c37d49150722}" title="Zermatt" class="c-btn c-btn--secondary c-btn c-btn--mid c-btn--secondary-hollow c-btn--wide u-text-center" data-anchor="#">Find Out More About Zermatt</a></p>
<p><a href="tel:01483791111" class="InfinityNumber c-btn">Call Us to Book Today</a></p>
<p><em>Please note: This is an independent multi-centre holiday and you are free to choose your own itinerary in each destination. The above contains recommendations which are provided for information only and are not included in the price of your holiday. An Inghams Destination Expert will be on hand locally either in resort or by telephone and will provide advice and offer optional excursions and walking passes.</em></p>
<p><em>Special diets, including vegetarian, must be requested prior to booking.</em></p>
<p><em>The itineraries may be subject to change. Where this becomes necessary, and where practicable, we will take the steps as outlined in clause 5 of our <a data-udi="umb://document/b703ff07ccec43baad41fffcfcc61821" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b703ff07ccec43baad41fffcfcc61821}" title="Terms &amp; Conditions">terms and conditions</a>.</em></p>]]></locationDescription>
